'''''Adocus beatus''''' is an extinct species of aquatic [[turtle]]s belonging to the family [[Adocidae]]. 
[[File: Peabody Museum Yale-189.jpg|thumb|180 px|left|Shell and skeleton of ''Adocus beatus'', [[Peabody Museum of Natural History]] ]]

==Description==
''Adocus beatus'' had flattened and smoothly contoured shells with horny sculptured plates. The shells could reach a length of about 80&nbsp;cm.

==Distribution==
These turtles have been found in Cretaceous to Paleogene of United States.

